result.execSummary:
The defendant Drew C Lara was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Drew C Lara in court with attorney Cole J White.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Minute sheet. State amends charge to Misd. bail jumping with the repeater enhancer. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters guilty plea to amended charge. Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty of misdemeanor bail jumping. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.
